text.tspan: In the UVM run phase, the dv_base_test class (from which the
aon_timer_base_test class derives) creates and runs the sequence
Many classes have handles (always called cfg) to the test's
aon_timer_env_cfg object. To denote this, those classes are connected by a
dotted line to the aon_timer_env_cfg class.
The virtual sequence object created in the run phase has a
p_sequencer handle to the aon_timer_virtual_sequencer inside the environment
Nesting shows fields in classes, so there is an object of type aon_timer_env inside
the object of type aon_timer_base_test.The color of the box for a class shows the
base class. For example, interfaces are pink; agents are green.
